Abstract = {{This paper is devoted to congruences and ideals in pseudoeffect
   algebras. Let I be a normal ideal in a pseudoeffect algebra E. We show
   that: (1) the relation similar to (I) induced by I is a congruence if
   and only if for every a is an element of E, I boolean AND {[}0,a] is
   upper directed; (2) the relation similar to (I) induced by I is a strong
   congruence if and only if I is a normal weak Riesz ideal in a
   pseudoeffect algebra E. Moreover, we introduce a stronger concept of
   congruence-namely Riesz strong congruence-and we prove that, if I is a
   normal weak Riesz ideal in a pseudoeffect algebra E, then similar to (I)
   is a Riesz strong congruence and, conversely, if similar to is a Riesz
   strong congruence, then I = {[}0](similar to) is a normal weak Riesz
   ideal, and similar to(I) = similar to.}},
